aa(lp42
VThe way we work is that we give people information.
p43
aVWe talk to the family members and we let them choose.
p44
aVWe let them decide to tell us the stories,
p45
aVto tell us what they saw,
p46
aVto tell us about their loved ones.
p47
aVAnd even more important,
p48
aVwe let them choose to give us a piece of themselves.
p49
aVA piece, an essence, of who they are.
p50
aVAnd that DNA is what we're  going to compare
p51
aVto the DNA that comes from the skeletons.
p52
aa(lp53
VWhile we're doing that, though, we're looking for the bodies.
p54
aVAnd these are skeletons by now,
p55
aVmost of these crimes  happened 32 years ago.
p56
aVWhen we find the grave,
p57
aVwe take out the dirt and eventually clean  the body, document it, and exhume it.
p58
aVWe literally bring the  skeleton out of the ground.
