aa(lp60
VOnce we have those bodies, though, we take them back to the city, to our lab,
p61
aVand we begin a process of trying to understand mainly two things:
p62
aVOne is how people died.
p63
aVSo here you see a gunshot wound to the back of the head
p64
aVor a machete wound, for example.
p65
aVThe other thing we want to understand is who they are.
p66
aVWhether it's a baby,
p67
aVor an adult.
p68
aVWhether it's a woman or a man.
p69
aVBut when we're done with that analysis
p70
aVwhat we'll do is we'll take a small  fragment of the bone
p71
aVand we'll extract DNA from it.
p72
aVWe'll take that DNA
p73
aVand then we'll compare it with the DNA of the families, of course.
