aVWhat we did is we conducted an exhumation in 2003,
p88
aVwhere we exhumed 220 bodies from 53 graves in a military base.
p89
aVGrave 9, though, matched the family of Sergio Saul Linares.
p90
aVNow Sergio was a professor at the university.
p91
aVHe graduted from Iowa State University
p92
aVand went back to Guatemala to change his country.
p93
aVAnd he was captured on  February 23, 1984.
p94
aVAnd if you can see there, he was  executed on March 29, 1984,
p95
aVwhich was incredible.
p96
aVWe had the body, we had the family's  information and their DNA,
p97
aVand now we have documents that told us exactly what happened.
