aa(lp117
VThe other case I want to tell you about
p118
aVis that of a military base  called CREOMPAZ.
p119
aVIt actually means, "to believe in peace," but the acronym really means
p120
aVRegional Command Center for Peacekeeping Operations.
p121
aVAnd this is where the Guatemalan military trains peacekeepers from other countries,
p122
aVthe ones that serve with the U.N.
p123
aVand go to countries like Haiti and the Congo.
p124
aVWell, we have testimony that said that within this military base,
p125
aVthere were bodies, there were graves.
p126
aVSo we went in there with a search warrant and about two hours after we went in,
p127
aVwe found the first of 84 graves,  a total of 533 bodies.
p128
aVNow, if you think about that,
p129
aVpeacekeepers being trained on top of bodies.
p130
aVIt's very ironic.
p131
aa(lp132
VBut the bodies \u2014 face down, most of them, hands tied behind their backs,
p133
aVblindfolded, all types of trauma \u2014
p134
aVthese were people who were defenseless who were being executed.
p135
aVPeople that 533 families are looking for.
p136
aVSo we're going to focus on Grave 15.
